 AFRICAN National Congress' Secretary General, Ace Magashule has reportedly been issued with a warrant of arrest. The details around the story are still sketchy at the moment, but it is believed to be in relation with the Vrede Dairy project in the Free State province. IOL reported that Magashule confirmed that he was aware of his pending arrest. "I'm aware. I'm aware,“ he said. “It's going to be a Hollywood style type of thing. But we will see," Magashule said. More details to follow... 